DIRECTOR - SR. DIRECTOR, BIOSTATISTICS
Build and manage an efficient biostatistics department to support the
discovery, clinical development and regulatory needs of company. This
position will be responsible for planning and performing statistical
analysis for clinical trials, which includes the design,
implementation, analysis and reporting of clinical trials.
Participate in the preparation of INDs, NDAs, and other reports
required by management and regulatory agencies for drug programs.
Hire, train and manage staff of this new statistical department.
Respond to queries posed by senior management and regulatory agencies.
Responsible for providing statistical advice to clinical research,
data management, and regulatory staff.
Provide vision, management and technical expertise to build a core
statistics and data management function capable of supporting
discovery and clinical development. Ensure that company has the
necessary capabilities and staff to operate a core in-house
statistical function and effectively integrate all outsourced data by
effectively bringing the entire function in-house.

This position will provide statistical, clinical trial methodological,
and regulatory input to study teams: trial design, sample size
estimation, randomization, and statistical methods.   Responsible for
the analysis of clinical trial data, provide statistical input into
the reporting of clinical trial results, and clearly communicate
statistical results and concepts to non-statisticians.
Contribute ideas for more efficient and effective design and analysis
of the clinical trials.  Appoint, hire, train and manage all
department staff by setting clearly defined goals, timelines, and
reviewing the progress.

Qualifications:
Ph.D. in Statistics / Biostatistics with 5-10 years of related
experience working in various therapeutic areas and all phases of
clinical development.   Some experience with SAS programming  /
databases is a plus.
Position requires excellent and proven leadership skills, team
building skills, and exceptional written and oral communication
skills. Strong ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously.
Capable of representing the Company in statistical discussions with
the FDA and other major regulatory authorities worldwide.

Company offers an exciting, cutting-edge work environment,  the
opportunity to build this new department from the ground up,
competitive compensation package and full relocation package to San
Diego.

